task.summary:
Please note: rem are the units which are prefered to handle accesible web sites. Each rem is just by default translated to 16px.

We can define an easier way to reason about it:

If rem works in a 16 base, it means if we multiply it to 0.625 = 10

It means if we use:

html{
    font-size: 62.5%;
}

Each rem will be translated to 10px.

We have learnt how to split our styles architecture:

We have an entry point called styles.scss where we import all the partial styles

In _base.scss we declare the conversion between rem unit and pixels unit, and the font families
In _header.scss we style the background and colors. The point here is that we use BlockElementModule naming convention to split our classes so then instead of:

.header{
    h1{

    }
}

We omit nesting elements using:

.header{}
.header__title{}
.header__subtitle{}

